                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" hclass="sense" id="americanindian_sng_2" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">a member of any of the peoples who were the original people living in America, before people arrived from Europe</span></span> <span class="un" un="help">Some people dislike using the general terms <span class="eb">Native American</span> or <span class="eb">American Indian</span> to refer to any of the many different groups of <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/indigenous" title="indigenous definition"><span class="ndv">indigenous</span></a> people from North and South America. It is better to be more specific if you can, by mentioning a particular region or using the name of a particular <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/tribe" title="tribe definition"><span class="ndv">tribe</span></a> or <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/nation" title="nation definition"><span class="ndv">nation</span></a>.</span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
